.SH NAME
.PP
removeCataRG \- remove catalog replica group.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]\f[I]db.removeCataRG()\f[]\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
Sdb
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Remove catalog replica group, require that there is no data node and coord node
information on the catalog replica group, remove catalog replica group will
remove all catalog node in the replica group.
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
No parameters.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
On success, no return value.
.PP
On error, exception will be thrown.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
When exception happen, use getLastError() to get the error code and use
getLastErrMsg() to get error message.
For more detial, please reference to Troubleshooting.
.SH HISTORY
.PP
Since v1.10
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
Remove catalog replica group.
.RS 2
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ db.removeCataRG()
\f[]
.fi
.RE
